licks in, eventually the melee may try to attack the pet giving you the oppurtunity to use some nukes, ive heard scintillation&lt;sp&gt; is good. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrumples.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grumples</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 557<br> <font color=#333333>(4/2/02 2:40:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=80.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Is it possible to beat melle with a horse pvp?</span><hr size=1> An experienced melee will destroy you if he has the ability to run faster than you.  Luckily, most melees aren't that good, and it took me a year of playing a PvP warrior before I realized the trick to hitting people who were moving away from me.  The only time I ever lost to any mage was under these specific conditions:<br>
1) Their pet was SOW'd<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> and</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
2) I was not SOW'd<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> and</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
3) They got the jump on me<br>
<br>
Any other circumstance, the mage would end up losing.<br>
<br>
Horses are among the many fine new Luclin products that ruined PvP.<br>
<br>
And assuming we're talking about a PvP fight and not a duel, there's no way you'll kill the melee.  When he gets low on health, he'll ride off into the sunset, heal up a bit with the fungal tunic and then come attack again.  It will be a war of attrition that you can't win as a magician.<br>
<br>
Of course, if the melee has a primal bow, forget about it.  I had a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> rogue</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> shooting me for over 100 damage roughly every 3 seconds with a primal bow.  And rogue bow skill caps at like 75, right?  Christ.  Running figure 8's isn't going to save you from that crap.  Even with an epic pet beating on them, with the PvP pet damage nerf I'm pretty sure there's no way the rogue would die from the pet before he shot the mage to death.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
So anyway... no.<br>
